📊 Project & Dashboard Summary

The Vehicle Testing Accuracy Dashboard is an end-to-end data analytics solution developed to analyze and monitor vehicle testing performance. 
The project integrates a MySQL database, FastAPI backend, and Streamlit frontend to deliver real-time insights through interactive visualizations.

The dashboard provides a clear view of key metrics such as vehicle testing status, plant-wise performance, and DTC (Diagnostic Trouble Code) trends. 
Users can apply filters like date range and plant code to dynamically explore the data and identify patterns affecting testing accuracy.

The backend, built using FastAPI, serves as a bridge between the database and the dashboard by exposing RESTful APIs that return structured JSON data. 
This ensures efficient data retrieval and seamless communication between components.

The system architecture follows a modern pipeline:
User → Streamlit Dashboard → FastAPI API → MySQL Database, enabling scalable and maintainable data flow.

Overall, this project demonstrates practical implementation of:

1. Data extraction and transformation

2. Backend API development

3. Database integration

4. Interactive dashboard design

5. Real-time data visualization
